This paper discusses neural networks and their use in classification tasks, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the computational and memory benefits of fixing the classifier, which is relevant to the field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
